beer.beer_description: Night Call is a brand new 8% DIPA exclusively for Can Jam. This hazy orange glowing DIPA has notes of dense tropical fruit, pineapple juice, orange creamsicle, zebra stripe gum and a hint of vanilla. Hopped with Amarillo, Denali, Eukanot Cryo and Lemon Drop.

items.badge_description: There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 40 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 9!

beer.beer_description: This IPA is a sharp counterpoint to the resin, dank citrus of Falcon Smash. It's an incredibly light bodied soft and dry American IPA with impressions of tropical citrus and dark berry floral aromas. Hopped generously with Citra and Mosaic hops. This batch has been slammed with double the Mosaic and Citra dry hop additions. Watch out, she's lethal.

beer.beer_description: Our ever rotating DIPA makes its return featuring Citra, Vic Secret, and Amarillo. In addition to the hop varietals, we subbed in an experimental yeast blend to take us even further down the rabbit hole of what yeast and hops can do once theyre forced upon each otheras it were. Pouring in the traditional parlance of our time with its pale haze, we taste kiwi, lime citrus, and hints of strawberry with an almost vanilla cream silk like finish. Enjoy our experimentation into both the familiar and slightly unknown.

Our signature DIPA made with house ale yeast, no bitterness and a soft mouthfeel. Notes of soft, white peach, citrus confectioners sugar and freshly fallen pine from a massive dry hopping of Vic Secret, Citra and Falconer's Flight.

beer.beer_description: Our base IPA recipe and house yeast strain massively hopped with Citra.
This beer is a bright tropical cyclone featuring two of our favorite hop varietals Citra and Mosaic. Pillowy mouth feel backs up the pungent aromatics.
Our base IPA recipe and house yeast strain massively hopped with Citra.
Our flagship IPA. Dank hop character from dry hop of Falconer's Flight, and a proprietary blend of rotating hop varietals. Fermented with our house ale strain.
An incredibly light bodied, soft and dry American IPA with impressions of tropical citrus and dark berry floral aromas.  Hopped generously with Citra and Mosaic hops.

Our flagship DIPA overwhelmingly dry hopped with Mosaic and Simcoe.

Soft, smooth, dry and hugely hop-forward with notes of tropical fruit, pineapple, passion fruit and mango, balanced with hints of resin and pine.
Citra based, wheat pale ale. This beer has been fermented with our expressive house ale yeast, providing fruity esters to complement the heavy hop load you're about to consume.
The flagship DIPA in our Lockout Series, this huge juice bomb is dry hopped with hundreds of pounds of Mosaic. Expect dank aromas of pine, tangerine, blueberry and papaya.
100% Citra DIPA

Our signature DIPA made with house ale yeast, no perceived bitterness and a silky smooth mouthfeel. Notes of peach gummy rings, freshly cut pineapples and exotic island fruit from a massive dry hopping of Galaxy, Citra and El Dorado.
Our base IPA recipe and house yeast strain massively hopped with Citra.
Our base IPA recipe overwhelmingly dry-hopped with Vic Secret and Galaxy for a beer with zero perceived bitterness and heavy stone fruit aromatics.
Citrus, peach, mango and passionfruit aromas and flavors from a heavy dry hopping of Galaxy and Mosaic.  Zero bitterness DIPA with a soft mouthfeel.
Citra, Galaxy and Vic Secret hopped DIPA with notes of bright pineapple and peach gummy rings. Soft mouthfeel and zero perceived bitterness.

The Lockout Series returns. This time around we decided to throw the book at the hop profile. We are featuring a proprietary hop blend. Notes of bright citrus, apricot and peaches are showing up big time.
Packed with notes of pineapple creamsicle juice. We aggressively hopped this with Vic Secret, El Dorado and Azacca.
Soft, full-bodied IPA with low alcohol and bitterness.  Aggressively hopped with Mosaic.
This beer is a bright tropical cyclone featuring two of our favorite hop varietals Citra and Mosaic. Pillowy mouth feel backs up the pungent aromatics.

The hop aromatics from this juice will hit you square in the face. Soft bright tropical notes intersect with a small amount of dankness rounding it out. Notes of passionfruit, guava, mango and peaches. We doubled down on two of our favorite hop varietals Mosaic and Falconers flight for this new offering.

This IPA is a sharp counterpoint to the resin, dank citrus of Falcon Smash. It's an incredibly light bodied soft and dry American IPA with impressions of tropical citrus and dark berry floral aromas. Hopped generously with Citra and Mosaic hops. This batch has been slammed with double the Mosaic and Citra dry hop additions. Watch out, she's lethal.
The Answer collaboration featuring Citra, Mosaic, and El Dorado.

Single malt, single hop beer based on a British summer ale. Made with minimal hops and an expressive English ale strain which gives a fruity aroma. Perfect year-round session ale.  Treated with ClarityFerm to remove Gluten during fermentation.
Dank, bright citrus, orange zest and tangerine notes. We packed this incredibly soft and extremely palatable DIPA with Mosaic and Simcoe Cryo hop pellets.

We went back and forth on process and ingredients and this beer will show that. The group decided to split the malt bill from our house malt and Foams supplier Peterson Quality Malt out of Vermont. To further integrate this collab we will be doing 50/50 split of our Triple Crossing house yeast and Foam Brewers House yeast. This DIPA was aggressively hopped with Citra and Galaxy to round it out. Notes of soft pillowy peach and candied orange gummy rings.
DIPA Featuring Citra, El Dorado and Simcoe.

The Distance 6% DDH IPA in collaboration with our friends Foam Brewers. When the guys from Foam came down for Juicy Brews, we brewed a couple beers and this being the first to see the light of day. A delicately soft DDH IPA that consists of a 50/50 mix of each brewers house yeast and a generous hopping regime of Citra, Denali, and Galaxy. This collab has bold notes of ripe mango, key-lime pie, orange rind, sweet drippy pineapple.

DDH 6% IPA we brewed with our friend Adam from Charles Towne Fermentory. Adam brought up his house ale yeast when visiting for East Coast Covenant and we blended that with our house strain for this IPA. The collab was aggressively hopped with Citra and El Dorado and one of the highest per bbl on an IPA we have done. Notes of bright peach, oranges and guava.
Triple Crossing's salute to our Revolutionary brethren.
